The document outlines a study on the psychological threats posed by COVID-19 and their impact on well-being and adherence to public health behaviors. Several components are mentioned:

**Study 1:**
- **Sample:** Conducted between March 19-20, 2020, with 346 participants (160 male, 184 female, 2 other) from the U.S., predominantly White (80.9%). Of these, 193 participants also had completed related measures in October 2019.
